# Clean Minimalist Aesthetic Update

The user has requested to clean up the use of color across the landing page, enforcing a primarily black and white aesthetic and only using the accent color where absolutely necessary. This involves an aesthetic overhaul to make the landing page feel more premium, sleek, and minimalist.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The current landing page uses several colorful gradients (blue, green, purple, amber, rose) in the Use Cases section and blue `primary` spotlights in the Hero section. This plan removes those in favor of a strictly monochrome grayscale aesthetic (using foreground/neutral colors). Please review this to confirm this aligns with your expectation of a clean B&W vibe.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Documentation (Synchronization Protocol)

We will update the content docs to reflect the newly established aesthetic rules.

#### [MODIFY] [landing-content.md](file:///C:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/prod-adecos/docs/landing-content.md)
- Append an "Aesthetics & Design System" section explicitly stating that the landing page strictly follows a black/white minimalist theme with minimal accent colors.

---

### Landing Page Components

We will shift all major visual elements currently using brand or rainbow colors towards a neutral grayscale.

#### [MODIFY] [Hero.tsx](file:///C:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/prod-adecos/src/containers/landing/Hero.tsx)
- Change the background spotlight gradient from `var(--primary)` to use `var(--foreground)` with low opacity.
- Remove `shadow-primary/10` from the get started button, replacing it with a neutral shadow.
- Change `text-primary` on the "Learn More" social proof link to `text-foreground hover:opacity-80`.

#### [MODIFY] [LandingUseCases.tsx](file:///C:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/prod-adecos/src/containers/landing/LandingUseCases.tsx)
- Replace all rainbow gradients (blue, green, purple, amber, rose) in the `color` attribute of `useCases` with a clean `from-foreground/5 to-transparent` gradient.
- Replace rainbow icon colors (`text-blue-500`, `text-green-500`, etc.) with `text-foreground`.
- Change hover group text from `group-hover:text-primary` to `group-hover:text-foreground/80`.
- Remove the background `bg-primary/5` blur, changing it to `bg-foreground/5` or `bg-neutral-500/5` to maintain the depth without the color.
- Change the "Explore features" link from `text-primary` to `text-foreground`.

#### [MODIFY] [OrbGradient.tsx](file:///C:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/prod-adecos/src/containers/landing/OrbGradient.tsx)
- Change `from-primary/20 via-primary/10` and `from-primary/15` color mixes to use neutral/foreground values (`from-foreground/10 via-foreground/5`, etc.) to keep the ambient glow but in monochrome.

#### [MODIFY] [LandingTestimonial.tsx](file:///C:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/prod-adecos/src/containers/landing/LandingTestimonial.tsx)
- Change "Loved by" icons from `text-primary` to neutral (`text-foreground` or `text-muted-foreground`).

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> 1. Do you want to keep the "highlight-gradient" class (which uses slate colors `from-slate-900 to-slate-500`) as is, or do you want the hero title to be purely black/white without a gradient?
> 2. Are there any specific Call To Action (CTA) buttons where you *do* want the `primary` blue accent to remain, or should all buttons be monochrome (black background/white text)? The Hero button is already `bg-foreground text-background`, which perfectly matches a B&W vibe.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- We will review the source code to ensure `primary` and rainbow tailwind color classes are removed and superseded by `foreground`, `background`, and `neutral` classes.
- The user can run the local dev server (`npm run dev`) and inspect the visual cleanliness on both light and dark mode, confirming the removal of excess color.
